          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/By authors/ In order to determine tracer of boron",
                "and sulfur using heavy ion activation analysis(HIAA),",
                "yield curves and total cross sections for the",
                "B-11(O-18,n+p)Mg-27 and S-32(O-18,t)V-47 reactions",
                "were determined in the 15 to 44 MeV O-18 and 27 to",
                " 44 MeV O-18 energy ranges, respectively. The yields",
                "of characteristic gamma-rays (Mg-27 - E(gamma)=843 keV",
                "and V-47 - E(gamma)=511 keV) were detected either with",
                "a Ge(Li) detector or by coincidence measurements",
                "using two 3*3 NaI(Tl)scintillation detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
